14 WHEREAS, the "Pledge of the Day" initiative encourages civic education, reinforces the
15 values of democracy, and fosters a spirit of unity among students, educators, and families in
16 communities throughout Georgia; and
17 WHEREAS, by showcasing young students leading the Pledge of Allegiance on Atlanta
18 News First and PeachtreeTV, this initiative serves as an inspiration for schools, communities,
19 and media organizations to promote civic engagement at an early age; and
20 WHEREAS, it is fitting and proper to honor Atlanta News First (WANF-TV); Erik Schrader,
21 President and General Manager of Atlanta News First (WANF-TV); and all those involved
22 in the "Pledge of the Day" initiative for their efforts in enhancing civic engagement and
23 encouraging students to take pride in their country.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
25 the members of this body recognize and commend Atlanta News First (WANF-TV); Erik
26 Schrader, President and General Manager of Atlanta News First (WANF-TV); and
27 Representative Kim Schofield for their dedication to civic education through the "Pledge of
28 the Day" initiative and express appreciation for their leadership in fostering patriotism among
29 Georgia's youth.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to Atlanta
32 News First (WANF-TV); Erik Schrader, President and General Manager of Atlanta News
33 First (WANF-TV); and Representative Kim Schofield.
